  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Social Contract
Branch:       Political
Definition:   Legitimate authority derives from agreement among individuals
Philosopher:  Hobbes/Locke/Rousseau
Example:      People surrender freedoms to government for security and rights

Concept:      Phenomenology
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Philosophy must study first-person conscious experience directly
Philosopher:  Husserl/Heidegger
Example:      What is the structure of my experience of time or other people?

Concept:      Virtue Ethics
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Ethics is about developing virtuous character traits
Philosopher:  Aristotle
Example:      A courageous person acts courageously habitually; ethics is becoming good

============================================================
  SCIENCE FACTS
============================================================

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Newton's Second Law
Formula: F = ma
Note:    Force equals mass times acceleration; classical mechanics

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Bayes Theorem
Formula: P(A|B) = P(B|A)P(A)/P(B)
Note:    Updating probability based on new evidence

Domain:  Medicine
Topic:   Germ Theory
Formula: Microorganisms cause disease
Note:    Pasteur/Koch; foundation of modern medicine

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Euler's Identity
Formula: e^(iπ) + 1 = 0
Note:    Relates five fundamental constants; called most beautiful equation

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Central Limit Theorem
Formula: Sample means → normal distribution
Note:    Foundation of statistical inference and polling

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Nash Equilibrium
Branch:       Game Theory
Formula:      No player benefits from unilateral strategy change
Applications: Economics, AI, political science
Discoverer:   John Nash (1950)

Theorem/Law:  Fundamental Theorem of Calculus
Branch:       Calculus
Formula:      ∫[a,b] f'(x)dx = f(b) - f(a)
Applications: Physics, engineering, economics
Discoverer:   Newton/Leibniz (1670)

Theorem/Law:  Quadratic Formula
Branch:       Algebra
Formula:      x = (-b ± sqrt(b²-4ac))/2a
Applications: Engineering, physics
Discoverer:   Ancient Babylonians (2000)

